It appears that in the "slow" case the repro code is spinning in the pthread_yield() at line 107 - i.e., trying to allow the contender threads run, but the main thread immediately resumes.

    98        /* Wait until every thread is ready.  */
    99        dbgprintf ("Main thread before synchronizing for round %d\n", repeat);
   100        for (;;)
   101          {
   102            int ready_count = 0;
   103            for (i = 0; i < THREAD_COUNT; i++)
   104              ready_count += ready[i];
   105            if (ready_count == THREAD_COUNT)
   106              break;
   107            pthread_yield ();
   108          }
